{
  "texts": [
    "Currently, MatKG does not differentiate between causative and correlative relationships, as acknowledged in the 'limitations' section.",
    "However, even with this limitation, MatKG is a powerful knowledge base to query material science literature as shown in Fig. 2.",
    "In order to respond to the customized query \"What are the applications of TiO2\", the top ten triples with the subject 'TiO2' and the relation 'material-property' are extracted from MatKG.",
    "It is immediately seen that the top applications of TiO2 are as electrodes, for coating, as catalysts, for dye sensitized solar cells, photocatalysts etc.",
    "Following the same procedure it is seen that the top symmetry and phase labels associated with TiO2 are anatase, rutile, and perovskite."
  ]
}